name: cdk-monitoring-constructs
documentation_summary: The HTML text is about "cdk-monitoring-constructs," a Python package available on PyPI for monitoring AWS infrastructure using Amazon CloudWatch. It provides easy-to-use CDK constructs for adding alarms, generating CloudWatch dashboards, and extending the library with custom metrics or extensions. The package supports multiple programming languages and requires Python version 3.8 or newer. The latest version, 7.7.0, was released on February 12, 2024. It offers features for monitoring various AWS services like API Gateway, DynamoDB, Lambda, and more, with the ability to customize actions for alarms and create custom monitoring segments or dashboards. The project is licensed under the Apache-2.0 License and is maintained by the CDK Monitoring Constructs Team.
